article.headline: South Alabama 85, Arkansas St. 67
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Daon Merritt had 19 points and Ernest Little added 15 points and 12 rebounds to lead South Alabama to an 85-67 victory over Arkansas State on Sunday -- the 12th consecutive win for the Jaguars. Arkansas State (12-14, 7-7 Sun Belt Conference) was led by 19 points and 12 rebounds from Isaac Wells. Teammate Adrian Banks had 15 points. South Alabama (19-7, 13-2 SBC) began the game turning the ball over on their first three possessions, but then went on an 11-0 run to build a 11-4 lead through the first five minutes of the game. Leandro Buboltz had two 3-pointers during the run to spark the Jaguars. South Alabama led 44-32 at halftime. For the game, the Jaguars shot 49.2 percent on 32 of 65 from the floor and were 11 of 28 from beyond the arc. Arkansas State shot 41.3 percent from the field on 26 of 63 and were 11 of 25 from beyond the arc.
